FBIS4-34067 "drlat115_o_94001" FBIS-LAT-94-115 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 Colombia Terrorists Attack Caracol, RCN Repeater Stations Terrorists Attack Caracol, RCN Repeater Stations PA1406140594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 14 Jun 94 PA1406140594 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network Spanish BFN [From the "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] [Text] Attention: The first problem of the Fourth Ibero-American Summit in Cartagena arose when terrorists blew up the Caracol and Radio Cadena Nacional [RCN] repeater stations. The attack, for which no group has claimed responsibility, destroyed the stations' tuning boxes and insulators. Caracol is using special emergency frequencies and mobile telephones to cover the presidential summit.
